A FORMER community councillor tormented by vandals at his home was killed after he confronted yobs who turned up at his door late at night. Thug admits killing A FORMER community councillor tormented by vandals at his home was killed after he confronted yobs who turned up at his door late at night.William McLachlan, 57, bled to death in his garden in Largs, Ayrshire, after being struck with a Samurai sword. He was attacked by Jamie Cameron, 20, who was high on drink and drugs.Cameron admitted culpable homicide at the High Court in Glasgow. Sentence was deferred. 